nster" href="wiki/Sea_monster">sea monster</a> in <a title="Greek mythology" href="wiki/Greek_mythology">Greek mythology</a>, although it is often called "the <a title="Whale" href="wiki/Whale">whale</a>" today. Cetus is located in the region of the sky that contains other water-related constellations such as <a title="Aquarius (constellation)" href="wiki/Aquarius_(constellation)">Aquarius</a>, <a title="Pisces (constellation)" href="wiki/Pisces_(constellation)">Pisces</a>, and <a title="Eridanus (constellation)" href="wiki/Eridanus_(constellation)">Eridanus</a>.' WHERE code = 'cet';
