a:IPA_for_English">/</a></span></span>) is a small <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellation</a> in the southern sky. It is named after the <a title="Chameleon" href="wiki/Chameleon">chameleon</a>, a form of <a title="Lizard" href="wiki/Lizard">lizard</a>. It was first defined in the <a title="Sixteenth century" class="mw-redirect" href="wiki/Sixteenth_century">sixteenth century</a>.' WHERE code = 'cha';
UPDATE CONSTELLATIONS SET description = 'The <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellation</a><b>Circinus</b> is a small <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellation</a> in the southern sky, first defined in the 18th century. Its name is <a title="Latin" href="wiki/Latin">Latin</a> for <a title="Compass (drafting)" href="wiki/Compass_(drafting)">compass</a>, referring to the <a title="Technical drawing" href="wiki/Technical_drawing">drafting</a> tool used for drawing circles; it should not be confused with <a title="Pyxis" href="wiki/Pyxis">Pyxis</a>, a constellation that represents a <a title="Mariner&apos;s compass" class="mw-redirect" href="wiki/Mariner%27s_compass">mariner"s compass</a>.' WHERE code = 'cir';
