iki/Star">stars</a> form a semicircular arc. It was one of the 48 constellations listed by the 2nd century astronomer <a title="Ptolemy" href="wiki/Ptolemy">Ptolemy</a> and remains one of the 88 modern constellations.' WHERE code = 'crb';
UPDATE CONSTELLATIONS SET description = '<b>Crater</b> is a <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellation</a>. Its name is <a title="Latin" href="wiki/Latin">Latin</a> for <a title="Drinkware" class="mw-redirect" href="wiki/Drinkware">cup</a>, and in <a title="Greek mythology" href="wiki/Greek_mythology">Greek mythology</a> it is identified with the cup of the god <a title="Apollo (god)" class="mw-redirect" href="wiki/Apollo_(god)">Apollo</a>. It was one of the 48 constellations listed by the 2nd century astronomer <a title="Ptolemy" href="wiki/Ptolemy">Ptolemy</a>, and remains one of the 88 modern constellations. It is faint, with no <a title="Star" href="wiki/Star">star</a> brighter than third <a title="Apparent magnitude" href="wiki/Apparent_magnitude">magnitude</a>.' WHERE code = 'crt';
UPDATE CONSTELLATIONS SET description = '<b>Crux</b> (<span class="nowrap"><span title="pronunciation:"><img height="11" alt="play" width="11" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png"></img></span>&#xa0;<span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English">/</a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="primary stress follows" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">&#x2c8;</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="&apos;k&apos; in &apos;kind&apos;" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">k</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="&apos;r&apos; in &apos;rye&apos;" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">r</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="short &apos;u&apos; in &apos;bud&apos;" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">&#x28c;</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="&apos;k&apos; in &apos;kind&apos;" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">k</span></a></span><span class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key"><span title="&apos;s&apos; in &apos;sigh&apos;" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">s</span></a></span><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a title="Wikipedia:IPA for English" href="wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English">/</a></span></span>) is the <a title="List of constellations by area" href="wiki/List_of_constellations_by_area">smallest</a> of the 88 modern <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellations</a>, but is one of the most distinctive. Its name is <a title="Latin" href="wiki/Latin">Latin</a> for <a title="Cross" href="wiki/Cross">cross</a>, and it is dominated by a cross-shaped <a title="Asterism (astronomy)" href="wiki/Asterism_(astronomy)">asterism</a> that is commonly known as the <b>Southern Cross</b>.' WHERE code = 'cru';
UPDATE CONSTELLATIONS SET description = '<b>Corvus</b> is a small <a title="Constellation" href="wiki/Constellation">constellation</a> in the southern sky. Its name is <a title="Latin" href="wiki/Latin">Latin</a> for <a title="Raven" href="wiki/Raven">raven</a> or <a title="Crow" href="wiki/Crow">crow</a>. It includes only 11 stars visible to the <a title="Naked eye" href="wiki/Naked_eye">naked eye</a> (brighter than <a title="Magnitude (astronomy)" href="wiki/Magnitude_(astronomy)">magnitude</a> 5.5). It was one of the 48 constellations listed by <a title="Ptolemy" href="wiki/Ptolemy">Ptolemy</a>, who only counted 7 stars,<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> and it remains one of the 88 modern constellations.' WHERE code = 'crv';
